      "originalContent": "# GENPLATFORM MISSION: CORE ARCHITECTURE OVERHAUL\n# Priority: CRITICAL | Date: 2026-03-20\n# Upload to self-dev → send Telegram message to execute\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n## ⚠️ ABSOLUTE PROTECTED FILES — NEVER TOUCH\n- src/app/layout.tsx\n- src/components/layout/sidebar.tsx\n- src/components/layout/navbar.tsx\n- src/app/globals.css\n- src/app/dashboard/self-dev/**\n- src/app/api/self-dev/**\n- src/components/self-dev/**\n\n## ⚠️ EXECUTION RULES\n- Build and verify after EVERY task before moving to next\n- If build fails → rollback that task only, do NOT touch other files\n- Run: npm run build after each task\n- Context budget: keep each task under 8K tokens of context\n- After every 5 tasks: save progress summary to ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/PROGRESS.md\n- Use BOTH Claude accounts alternately to prevent rate limiting\n- Never stop execution — if Account 1 hits limit, switch to Account 2 immediately\n\n---\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PHASE A: FIX CRITICAL BUGS (do these FIRST)\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n## TASK-A1: Fix Claude Code page preview error\n**File**: src/app/dashboard/claude/page.tsx (or wherever Claude Code page is)\n**Problem**: Right panel shows \"Something went wrong!\" error\n**Fix**:\n1. Find the LivePreviewPanel component\n2. Add proper error boundary with try/catch\n3. The iframe src must start with https:// — add validation:\n   ```typescript\n   const safeUrl = url?.startsWith('http') ? url : `https://${url}`;\n   ```\n4. Add fallback UI when iframe fails to load:\n   ```tsx\n   <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center h-full text-sm text-muted\">\n     <p>Select a project to see live preview</p>\n   </div>\n   ```\n5. Default state (no project selected) should show the fallback, NOT an error\n**Verify**: Open /dashboard/claude — right panel should show fallback message, NOT error\n\n---\n\n## TASK-A2: Fix context window leak — prevent system from stopping\n**Problem**: System stops unexpectedly when working from web UI. Root cause is likely\ncontext accumulation — conversation history grows too large.\n\n**Fix in Bridge API** (src/app/api/bridge/ or genplatform-api/):\n1. Find the function that sends messages to OpenClaw/Claude\n2. Add context trimming: keep only last 15 messages maximum:\n   ```typescript\n   const MAX_HISTORY = 15;\n   if (messages.length > MAX_HISTORY) {\n     messages = [messages[0], ...messages.slice(-MAX_HISTORY + 1)];\n     // Keep system prompt (index 0) + last 14 messages\n   }\n   ```\n3. Add token estimation before each API call:\n   ```typescript\n   const estimatedTokens = JSON.stringify(messages).length / 4;\n   if (estimatedTokens > 150000) { // 150K safety threshold before 200K limit\n     // Reset to system prompt only + last 5 messages\n     messages = [messages[0], ...messages.slice(-5)];\n     // Log the reset\n     console.log('[CONTEXT RESET] Token limit approaching, trimmed history');\n   }\n   ```\n4. Save context state to file every 10 messages:\n   ```typescript\n   // Write to ~/.openclaw/workspace/current-task.json\n   // Max 450 bytes summary, NOT full conversation\n   ```\n\n**Verify**: Check that conversations don't accumulate in memory logs\n\n---\n\n## TASK-A3: Fix cascading bugs — add atomic task execution\n**Problem**: Fixing one bug creates another. This happens because tasks modify\nshared files without checking current state first.\n\n**Fix**: Add a pre-execution check in self-dev system:\n1. Open src/app/api/self-dev/execute/route.ts (or similar)\n2. Before executing any task, add file state snapshot:\n   ```typescript\n   // Before modifying any file\n   const fileContent = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');\n   const backup = { path: filePath, content: fileContent, timestamp: Date.now() };\n   await saveBackup(backup); // save to /tmp/task-backup/\n   ```\n3. After execution, run build check:\n   ```typescript\n   const buildResult = await exec('cd /root/genplatform && npm run build 2>&1');\n   if (buildResult.includes('Error') || buildResult.includes('Failed')) {\n     // Restore backup\n     await restoreBackup(backup);\n     return { status: 'rolled_back', reason: buildResult };\n   }\n   ```\n4. Each task should be ATOMIC — either fully succeeds or fully reverts\n\n---\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PHASE B: RESTRUCTURE IDEAS INTO PROJECTS\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n## TASK-B1: Remove Ideas from sidebar navigation\n**Goal**: Ideas are no longer a standalone page — they live INSIDE each project\n\n1. Open src/components/layout/sidebar.tsx\n   ⚠️ PROTECTED — do NOT edit this file\n   \n2. Instead: update the routing so /dashboard/ideas redirects to /dashboard/projects\n   Create file: src/app/dashboard/ideas/page.tsx\n   ```typescript\n   import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';\n   export default function IdeasPage() {\n     redirect('/dashboard/projects');\n   }\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-B2: Rebuild Project Creation Flow\n**File**: src/app/dashboard/projects/new/page.tsx (create if not exists)\n\n**The flow**:\nStep 1 — Name + Description (with AI idea expansion)\nStep 2 — Subdomain assignment\nStep 3 — Tech stack selection\nStep 4 — Confirm → Create project + assign subdomain\n\n**UI for Step 1** — large textarea with AI assist:\n```tsx\n<div className=\"space-y-4\">\n  <h2 className=\"text-sm font-medium\">Describe your project idea</h2>\n  <p className=\"text-xs text-muted\">Write anything — even 3 sentences. \n     AI will extract and expand the full details.</p>\n  <textarea\n    placeholder=\"Example: I want to build a platform that lets users create AI-powered chatbots for their websites without coding...\"\n    className=\"w-full h-40 bg-background-secondary border border-border-tertiary \n               rounded-lg p-4 text-sm resize-none\"\n    onChange={(e) => setIdeaText(e.target.value)}\n  />\n  <button onClick={handleAIExpand}>\n    Analyze with AI →\n  </button>\n</div>\n```\n\n**After AI analysis** — show extracted fields (editable):\n- Project name (auto-generated from idea)\n- Short description (1 line)\n- Key features list (expandable)\n- Suggested subdomain: [slug].gen3.ai\n\n**API call**: POST /api/projects/analyze-idea\n```typescript\n// Takes raw idea text → returns structured project data\nbody: { ideaText: string }\nresponse: {\n  name: string,\n  description: string,\n  slug: string,\n  features: string[],\n  techStack: string[],\n  estimatedPages: { name: string, role: string }[]\n}\n```\n\n**Subdomain logic** (Step 2):\n```typescript\nconst slug = ideaText\n  .split(' ').slice(0, 3).join('-')\n  .toLowerCase()\n  .replace(/[^a-z0-9-]/g, '');\n// Show: slug.gen3.ai → editable input\n```\n\n**On Confirm** → call POST /api/projects/create:\n```typescript\nbody: { name, description, slug, techStack, ideaText }\n// Server does:\n// 1. Save project to database\n// 2. Create Caddy entry: slug.gen3.ai → port X\n// 3. Create project directory: /root/projects/slug/\n// 4. Initialize git repo\n// 5. Redirect to /dashboard/projects/[id]\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-B3: Rebuild Project Detail Page — Pipeline as Homepage\n**File**: src/app/dashboard/projects/[id]/page.tsx\n\nThis is the MAIN page when you click a project. Default tab = Pipeline.\n\n**Layout**:\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex flex-col h-full\">\n  {/* Header */}\n  <ProjectHeader project={project} />\n  \n  {/* Tabs */}\n  <ProjectTabs tabs={['Pipeline', 'Chat', 'Tasks', 'Preview', 'Quality', 'Settings']} />\n  \n  {/* Tab Content */}\n  {activeTab === 'pipeline' && <PipelineView project={project} />}\n  {activeTab === 'chat' && <ProjectChatView project={project} />}\n  {activeTab === 'tasks' && <ProjectTasksView project={project} />}\n  {activeTab === 'preview' && <ProjectPreviewView project={project} />}\n</div>\n```\n\n**Header component** (src/components/projects/ProjectHeader.tsx):\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex items-center justify-between p-4 border-b border-border-tertiary\">\n  <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3\">\n    {/* Color square with initials */}\n    <div className=\"w-9 h-9 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-medium\"\n         style={{ background: project.color }}>\n      {project.initials}\n    </div>\n    <div>\n      <h1 className=\"text-sm font-medium\">{project.name}</h1>\n      <p className=\"text-xs text-muted\">\n        {project.status} — {project.progress}% — \n        <a href={`https://${project.subdomain}.gen3.ai`} target=\"_blank\" \n           className=\"text-info ml-1\">{project.subdomain}.gen3.ai</a>\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <button className=\"text-xs border border-border-tertiary rounded px-3 py-1.5\">\n    Open Chat\n  </button>\n</div>\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-B4: Build Interactive Pipeline Component\n**File**: src/components/projects/PipelineView.tsx\n\n**7 stages with click-to-expand**:\n```tsx\nconst STAGES = [\n  { id: 'idea',     icon: '💡', label: 'Idea',        color: 'green'  },\n  { id: 'analysis', icon: '🔬', label: 'Analysis',    color: 'green'  },\n  { id: 'planning', icon: '📋', label: 'Planning',    color: 'green'  },\n  { id: 'dev',      icon: '💻', label: 'Development', color: 'amber'  },\n  { id: 'review',   icon: '🔍', label: 'Review',      color: 'gray'   },\n  { id: 'security', icon: '🛡️', label: 'Security',    color: 'gray'   },\n  { id: 'deploy',   icon: '✅', label: 'Deploy',      color: 'gray'   },\n];\n```\n\n**When clicking a stage** → show StageDetailPanel:\n\n### Clicking \"Idea\" stage shows:\n- Original idea text (read-only)\n- AI expansion result (what AI understood)\n- Approved features list\n\n### Clicking \"Analysis\" stage shows:\nFull analysis breakdown in sections:\n```\n📊 Market Analysis\n  - Target audience\n  - Competitors table (Name | Strengths | Weaknesses | Our advantage)\n  - Market size estimate\n\n✨ Recommended Features\n  - Core features (must-have)\n  - Enhancement features (can-add)\n  \n🛠️ Tech Stack\n  - Frontend | Backend | Database | AI Models | DevOps\n\n🤖 AI Tools & Skills (from ClawHub)\n  - Which AI models to use and for what purpose\n  - Open source alternatives\n\n📄 Pages & Their Roles\n  - List of all pages the project needs\n  - Each page: name + role + key components\n  \n💰 Cost Estimation\n  - Monthly infrastructure cost\n  - AI API costs\n  - Total estimate\n\n⏱️ Timeline\n  - MVP: X weeks\n  - Full version: X months\n```\n\n### Clicking \"Planning\" stage shows:\nFull technical planning:\n```\n🏗️ Architecture Overview\n  - System diagram description\n  - Data flow\n\n📁 File Structure\n  - Complete folder tree\n  - Key files and their purpose\n\n🗄️ Database Schema\n  - Tables / Collections\n  - Relationships\n\n🔌 API Endpoints\n  - Complete list with method, path, body, response\n\n📋 Development Tasks (auto-generated)\n  - Broken into: Frontend | Backend | Database | AI | DevOps\n  - Each task: ID | Description | Estimated hours | Dependencies\n  - Tasks should be GRANULAR (50-200 tasks minimum for a real project)\n```\n\n### Clicking \"Development\" stage shows:\n- Current tasks in progress\n- Agents working\n- Live execution log\n- Progress: X/Y tasks\n\n### Clicking \"Review\" stage shows:\n- Code review checklist\n- Quality metrics\n- Issues found\n\n### Clicking \"Security\" stage shows:\n- Security scan results\n- Vulnerabilities (if any)\n- Compliance checklist\n\n### Clicking \"Deploy\" stage shows:\n- Deployment history\n- Live URL\n- Performance metrics\n- Uptime status\n\n**Implementation**:\n```tsx\nconst [selectedStage, setSelectedStage] = useState<string | null>(null);\n\nreturn (\n  <div>\n    {/* Pipeline horizontal row */}\n    <div className=\"flex items-center gap-0 overflow-x-auto p-6\">\n      {STAGES.map((stage, i) => (\n        <>\n          <StageNode \n            key={stage.id}\n            stage={stage}\n            data={stageData[stage.id]}\n            isActive={selectedStage === stage.id}\n            onClick={() => setSelectedStage(stage.id === selectedStage ? null : stage.id)}\n          />\n          {i < STAGES.length - 1 && <StageConnector status={getConnectorStatus(i)} />}\n        </>\n      ))}\n    </div>\n    \n    {/* Stats row */}\n    <StatsRow project={project} />\n    \n    {/* Stage detail panel — shows when stage is selected */}\n    {selectedStage && (\n      <StageDetailPanel \n        stage={selectedStage}\n        project={project}\n        onClose={() => setSelectedStage(null)}\n      />\n    )}\n    \n    {/* Default view when no stage selected */}\n    {!selectedStage && (\n      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 p-6\">\n        <ActiveAgentsPanel project={project} />\n        <ExecutionLogPanel project={project} />\n      </div>\n    )}\n    \n    {/* Control bar */}\n    <ProjectControlBar project={project} />\n  </div>\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-B5: Deep AI Idea Analysis System\n**File**: src/app/api/projects/analyze-idea/route.ts\n\nThis is the CORE intelligence. When user submits even 3-5 lines, \nthe AI must extract EVERYTHING.\n\n```typescript\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  const { ideaText, projectId } = await req.json();\n  \n  const systemPrompt = `You are an expert product strategist and technical architect.\nYour job is to take ANY idea description (even vague) and produce an EXHAUSTIVE, \nPROFESSIONAL analysis that covers every aspect needed to build it.\n\nRULES:\n- Never give generic advice — be specific to THIS idea\n- Extract implied features the user didn't mention but would obviously want\n- Suggest AI tools from: OpenAI, Anthropic, Hugging Face, open source models\n- Identify ALL pages/screens the product needs\n- Be granular — a \"dashboard page\" is not enough, list what's IN the dashboard\n- Cost estimates should be realistic monthly figures\n- Tech stack should be modern but not over-engineered\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT: Respond in valid JSON only, no markdown, no explanation outside JSON.`;\n\n  const userPrompt = `Idea: \"${ideaText}\"\n  \nReturn this exact JSON structure:\n{\n  \"projectName\": \"...\",\n  \"tagline\": \"one line description\",\n  \"problemSolved\": \"what exact problem this solves\",\n  \"targetAudience\": [\"primary\", \"secondary\"],\n  \"coreFeatures\": [\n    { \"name\": \"...\", \"description\": \"...\", \"priority\": \"must|should|nice\" }\n  ],\n  \"enhancementIdeas\": [\n    { \"name\": \"...\", \"description\": \"...\", \"valueAdd\": \"why this increases value\" }\n  ],\n  \"competitors\": [\n    { \"name\": \"...\", \"strengths\": \"...\", \"weaknesses\": \"...\", \"ourAdvantage\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n  \"techStack\": {\n    \"frontend\": \"...\",\n    \"backend\": \"...\",\n    \"database\": \"...\",\n    \"hosting\": \"...\",\n    \"aiModels\": [{ \"model\": \"...\", \"useCase\": \"...\", \"cost\": \"...\" }],\n    \"openSourceAlternatives\": [\"...\"]\n  },\n  \"clawHubSkills\": [\n    { \"skill\": \"...\", \"purpose\": \"...\", \"implementation\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n  \"pages\": [\n    { \n      \"name\": \"...\", \n      \"route\": \"/...\", \n      \"role\": \"what this page does\",\n      \"keyComponents\": [\"...\"],\n      \"dataNeeded\": [\"...\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"databaseSchema\": [\n    { \"table\": \"...\", \"fields\": [\"id\", \"...\"], \"relationships\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n  \"apiEndpoints\": [\n    { \"method\": \"GET|POST|PUT|DELETE\", \"path\": \"/api/...\", \"purpose\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n  \"costEstimation\": {\n    \"hosting\": \"$X/month\",\n    \"aiApis\": \"$X/month\", \n    \"thirdPartyServices\": \"$X/month\",\n    \"total\": \"$X/month\"\n  },\n  \"timeline\": {\n    \"mvp\": \"X weeks\",\n    \"fullVersion\": \"X months\",\n    \"phases\": [\"Phase 1: ...\", \"Phase 2: ...\"]\n  },\n  \"riskFactors\": [\"...\"],\n  \"successMetrics\": [\"...\"]\n}`;\n\n  // Call Claude API\n  const response = await callClaudeAPI(systemPrompt, userPrompt);\n  const analysis = JSON.parse(response);\n  \n  // Save to database\n  await saveAnalysis(projectId, analysis);\n  \n  return NextResponse.json({ analysis });\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-B6: Project Chat Tab — Idea Refinement Interface\n**File**: src/components/projects/ProjectChatView.tsx\n\nThis is the \"Chat with your idea\" interface — different from the main Claude Code chat.\n\nPurpose: User can discuss and refine the idea/analysis in natural language.\n\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex flex-col h-full\">\n  <div className=\"p-4 border-b border-border-tertiary\">\n    <p className=\"text-xs text-muted\">\n      Discuss and refine your project idea. Changes are applied to the Analysis stage.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  \n  {/* Messages */}\n  <div className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 space-y-3\">\n    {messages.map(msg => <ChatMessage key={msg.id} message={msg} />)}\n  </div>\n  \n  {/* Input */}\n  <div className=\"p-4 border-t border-border-tertiary\">\n    <textarea\n      placeholder=\"Ask anything about your project, suggest changes, add features...\"\n      className=\"w-full bg-background-secondary border border-border-tertiary \n                 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm resize-none h-20\"\n    />\n    <div className=\"flex justify-between mt-2\">\n      <span className=\"text-xs text-muted\">Changes will update the Analysis stage</span>\n      <button className=\"text-xs border border-border-tertiary rounded px-3 py-1.5\">\n        Send (Ctrl+Enter)\n      </button>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n**STRICT DATA RULES** (implement in API):\n```typescript\n// POST /api/projects/[id]/chat\n// When user asks to ADD something:\n// → Merge with existing analysis, NEVER delete existing data\n// → Mark new items with source: 'user_addition'\n\n// When user asks to REMOVE something:\n// → Delete from analysis object\n// → Do NOT keep in database at all (permanent removal)\n// → Log removal: \"User removed: X at timestamp\"\n\n// When user asks to MODIFY something:\n// → Update the specific field only\n// → Keep old value in history: { current: \"new\", previous: \"old\" }\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-B7: Generate Development Tasks from Planning\n**File**: src/app/api/projects/[id]/generate-tasks/route.ts\n\nAfter Planning stage is complete, user can trigger task generation.\n\n```typescript\nconst taskGenerationPrompt = `\nYou are a senior technical project manager.\nBased on this project analysis, generate a COMPLETE, GRANULAR task list.\n\nRules:\n- MINIMUM 50 tasks for any real project, up to 500 for complex ones\n- Each task must be completable in 1-8 hours\n- Tasks must have clear dependencies (which tasks must finish first)\n- Assign each task to a department: Frontend | Backend | Database | AI | DevOps | QA | Security\n- Task IDs format: DEPT-XXX (e.g., FE-001, BE-001, DB-001)\n- Priority: critical | high | medium | low\n- Include setup tasks (repo, CI/CD, env vars, etc.)\n- Include testing tasks for every feature\n- Include documentation tasks\n\nOutput JSON array:\n[{\n  \"id\": \"FE-001\",\n  \"title\": \"...\",\n  \"description\": \"detailed description of exactly what to do\",\n  \"department\": \"Frontend\",\n  \"estimatedHours\": 3,\n  \"priority\": \"critical\",\n  \"dependencies\": [\"DB-001\", \"BE-002\"],\n  \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\"...\", \"...\"]\n}]\n`;\n```\n\n---\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PHASE C: DUAL ACCOUNT MANAGEMENT — NEVER STOP WORKING\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n## TASK-C1: Implement account rotation in Bridge API\n**File**: genplatform-api/src/routes/gateway.js (or similar)\n\n**Problem**: Single account hits rate limits → system stops\n**Solution**: Rotate between 2 Claude Pro Max accounts seamlessly\n\n```javascript\n// Account pool configuration\nconst ACCOUNTS = [\n  { id: 'account1', sessionPath: '/root/.config/claude/session1.json', status: 'active', lastUsed: 0 },\n  { id: 'account2', sessionPath: '/root/.config/claude/session2.json', status: 'active', lastUsed: 0 }\n];\n\nlet currentAccountIndex = 0;\n\nfunction getNextAccount() {\n  // Round-robin selection\n  const account = ACCOUNTS[currentAccountIndex];\n  currentAccountIndex = (currentAccountIndex + 1) % ACCOUNTS.length;\n  return account;\n}\n\nasync function executeWithFallback(command, options = {}) {\n  const primaryAccount = getNextAccount();\n  \n  try {\n    return await executeWithAccount(command, primaryAccount, options);\n  } catch (error) {\n    if (error.message.includes('rate limit') || error.message.includes('limit exceeded')) {\n      console.log(`[ACCOUNT ROTATION] ${primaryAccount.id} rate limited, switching...`);\n      \n      // Try other account\n      const fallbackAccount = ACCOUNTS.find(a => a.id !== primaryAccount.id);\n      if (fallbackAccount) {\n        return await executeWithAccount(command, fallbackAccount, options);\n      }\n      \n      // Both limited — wait 60 seconds and retry\n      console.log('[ACCOUNT ROTATION] Both accounts limited, waiting 60s...');\n      await sleep(60000);\n      return await executeWithAccount(command, primaryAccount, options);\n    }\n    throw error;\n  }\n}\n\n// Health check — ping accounts every 5 minutes\nsetInterval(async () => {\n  for (const account of ACCOUNTS) {\n    try {\n      await checkAccountStatus(account);\n      account.status = 'active';\n    } catch {\n      account.status = 'degraded';\n      console.log(`[ACCOUNT HEALTH] ${account.id} is degraded`);\n    }\n  }\n}, 5 * 60 * 1000);\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-C2: Implement execution queue — web UI parity with Telegram\n**Problem**: Web UI sends tasks but system stops. Telegram works fine.\n**Root cause**: Web requests have timeout (30s). Long-running tasks timeout and appear stopped.\n**Solution**: Queue-based execution with SSE streaming\n\n**File**: genplatform-api/src/services/ExecutionQueue.js (create new)\n\n```javascript\nclass ExecutionQueue {\n  constructor() {\n    this.queue = [];\n    this.running = false;\n    this.clients = new Map(); // SSE clients\n  }\n  \n  addTask(taskId, command, projectId) {\n    this.queue.push({ taskId, command, projectId, status: 'queued', addedAt: Date.now() });\n    this.emit('task_queued', { taskId, position: this.queue.length });\n    \n    if (!this.running) this.processNext();\n    return taskId;\n  }\n  \n  async processNext() {\n    if (this.queue.length === 0) { this.running = false; return; }\n    \n    this.running = true;\n    const task = this.queue.shift();\n    task.status = 'running';\n    \n    this.emit('task_started', { taskId: task.taskId });\n    \n    try {\n      // Execute via OpenClaw/Claude\n      const result = await executeWithFallback(task.command);\n      \n      task.status = 'completed';\n      this.emit('task_completed', { taskId: task.taskId, result });\n      \n      // Save to progress\n      await updateProgress(task.taskId, 'completed', result);\n      \n    } catch (error) {\n      task.status = 'failed';\n      this.emit('task_failed', { taskId: task.taskId, error: error.message });\n      \n      // Auto-retry once\n      if (!task.retried) {\n        task.retried = true;\n        this.queue.unshift(task); // Put back at front\n      }\n    }\n    \n    // Always continue to next task\n    setTimeout(() => this.processNext(), 500);\n  }\n  \n  // SSE: subscribe to task updates\n  subscribe(clientId, res) {\n    this.clients.set(clientId, res);\n    res.on('close', () => this.clients.delete(clientId));\n  }\n  \n  emit(event, data) {\n    const message = `data: ${JSON.stringify({ event, ...data })}\\n\\n`;\n    this.clients.forEach(client => {\n      try { client.write(message); } catch { }\n    });\n    \n    // Also send to Telegram\n    sendTelegramUpdate(`[Queue] ${event}: ${JSON.stringify(data)}`);\n  }\n}\n\nconst queue = new ExecutionQueue();\nmodule.exports = { queue };\n```\n\n**Add SSE endpoint** in Bridge API:\n```javascript\n// GET /api/queue/stream\napp.get('/api/queue/stream', (req, res) => {\n  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');\n  res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');\n  res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive');\n  \n  const clientId = Date.now().toString();\n  queue.subscribe(clientId, res);\n  \n  // Send current status immediately\n  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({ event: 'connected', queue: queue.getStatus() })}\\n\\n`);\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PHASE D: CONTEXT WINDOW MANAGEMENT VERIFICATION\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n## TASK-D1: Verify and enforce context window rules\n**File**: ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/WORK-RULES.md (check and update)\n\nVerify these rules exist and are enforced:\n\n```markdown\n## CONTEXT WINDOW RULES (200K limit)\n\n### Budget allocation:\n- System prompt: max 2K tokens\n- Memory/context files: max 5K tokens\n- Current task: max 500 bytes (NOT full conversation)\n- Conversation history: max 15 messages\n- Code files in context: max 50K tokens total\n- Response buffer: 20K tokens\n- Safety margin: 20K tokens\n- Working budget: ~100K tokens for actual work\n\n### Auto-reset triggers:\n- After every 30 tasks: full context reset\n- When usage reaches 80% (160K/200K): soft reset (keep last 5 messages)\n- When usage reaches 90% (180K/200K): hard reset (system prompt only)\n- Never include full file contents — use line ranges instead\n\n### What goes in current-task.json (max 450 bytes):\n{\n  \"task\": \"brief description\",\n  \"file\": \"path/to/file\",\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"nextStep\": \"what to do next\"\n}\n\n### What NEVER goes in context:\n- Full conversation history (> 15 messages)\n- Complete file contents (> 200 lines)\n- Multiple large files at once\n- Completed task details\n```\n\n**Implement context monitor** in Bridge API:\n```typescript\n// Add to every API call handler\nfunction checkContextUsage(messages: Message[]): number {\n  const totalChars = JSON.stringify(messages).length;\n  const estimatedTokens = Math.ceil(totalChars / 4);\n  const usagePercent = (estimatedTokens / 200000) * 100;\n  \n  if (usagePercent > 90) {\n    // Hard reset\n    return trimToSystemPrompt(messages);\n  } else if (usagePercent > 80) {\n    // Soft reset  \n    return trimToLast5(messages);\n  }\n  \n  return messages; // No trim needed\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK-D2: Add real-time context usage display\n**File**: src/components/projects/ProjectControlBar.tsx\n\nThe bottom control bar should show REAL context usage:\n\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex items-center gap-4 text-xs text-muted\">\n  <span>{completedTasks}/{totalTasks} tasks ({Math.round(progress)}%)</span>\n  <span>Context: {contextUsed}K/200K</span>\n  \n  {/* Color-coded warning */}\n  <span className={cn(\n    contextPercent > 80 ? 'text-danger' : \n    contextPercent > 60 ? 'text-warning' : \n    'text-success'\n  )}>\n    ({contextPercent}% used)\n  </span>\n  \n  <span>Est: {estimatedTimeRemaining}</span>\n</div>\n```\n\n**Fetch real context data** from Bridge API:\n```typescript\n// GET /api/bridge/context-status\n// Response: { used: 34000, total: 200000, percent: 17, resetCount: 2 }\n```\n\n---\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PHASE E: FINAL CLEANUP\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n## TASK-E1: Remove Tasks from sidebar (tasks live inside projects now)\nTasks page (/dashboard/tasks) should redirect to /dashboard/projects\n```typescript\n// src/app/dashboard/tasks/page.tsx — replace content with:\nimport { redirect } from 'next/navigation';\nexport default function TasksPage() {\n  redirect('/dashboard/projects');\n}\n```\n⚠️ Do NOT modify sidebar.tsx — just add the redirect\n\n## TASK-E2: Build final — verify all routes work\n```bash\ncd /root/genplatform\nnpm run build\npm2 restart genplatform-app\n```\nCheck these routes:\n- /dashboard/projects ✓\n- /dashboard/projects/new ✓\n- /dashboard/projects/[id] ✓ (with pipeline tabs)\n- /dashboard/claude ✓ (no error in preview panel)\n- /dashboard/ideas → redirects to /dashboard/projects ✓\n\n## TASK-E3: Send completion report to Telegram\nAfter all tasks complete, send summary:\n```\n✅ MISSION COMPLETE\n\nCompleted:\n- A1: Claude Code preview fixed\n- A2: Context leak fixed (max 15 messages)\n- A3: Atomic task execution (rollback on fail)\n- B1-B7: Ideas inside Projects (full pipeline)\n- C1: Dual account rotation\n- C2: Execution queue (web UI parity with Telegram)\n- D1-D2: Context window rules enforced + displayed\n- E1-E3: Cleanup + final build\n\nURLs to test:\n- /dashboard/projects — project list\n- /dashboard/projects/new — create with AI expansion\n- /dashboard/projects/[id] — pipeline view\n- /dashboard/claude — Claude Code (no error)\n\nContext window: [current usage]\nBuild: ✅\n```\n\n---\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# EXECUTION ORDER\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nExecute in this exact order:\n1. TASK-A1 (fix Claude Code error) — quick win\n2. TASK-A2 (context leak) — prevents stopping\n3. TASK-A3 (atomic execution) — prevents cascading bugs\n4. TASK-C1 (dual account) — ensures continuous work\n5. TASK-C2 (execution queue) — web UI parity\n6. TASK-B2 (project creation flow)\n7. TASK-B4 (pipeline component)\n8. TASK-B5 (AI analysis system) — CORE\n9. TASK-B3 (project detail page)\n10. TASK-B6 (project chat)\n11. TASK-B7 (task generation)\n12. TASK-B1 (ideas redirect)\n13. TASK-D1 (context rules)\n14. TASK-D2 (context display)\n15. TASK-E1 (tasks redirect)\n16. TASK-E2 (final build)\n17. TASK-E3 (completion report)\n\nTotal: 17 tasks\nBuild after each task.\nReport progress after every 5 tasks.\nNever stop — use account rotation if rate limited.",
